node.text: On the coast of Portugal, Gordon Ramsay visits one of the most unique vineyards on the planet where the vines grow in the sand. A new season of Gordon Ramsay: Uncharted airs Monday, May 31 at 9/8c.

node.title: Gordon Ramsay: Uncharted – A Vineyard in the Sand

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by National Geographic Travel on July 27, 2021. May be an image of outdoors and brick wall.

node.text:
Photo by Keith Ladzinski @ladzinski / While exploring downtown Quito, I spotted this incredible plant hanging from the side of a wall and had to make a photo with it. It was a quiet street, but I knew it was only a matter of time before a pedestrian would walk by and provide a bit of scale to the scene. Quito, the capital of Ecuador, is a high-altitude city perched at roughly 9,300 feet (2,835 meters). The must-see destination is rich with culture, art, and fantastic culinary cuisine. 
To see more of this beautiful part of the world, please visit @ladzinski.

node.text:
Photo by @sarah_stacke / The Moreau River, a tributary of the Missouri River, runs through the Cheyenne River Reservation, creating steep cut banks along the way. Home to the Cheyenne River Lakota Nation, the reservation covers 4,267 square miles (11,051 square kilometers) in the state of South Dakota and is the fourth largest reservation in the United States. The Missouri River forms the reservation’s eastern boundary and the Cheyenne River forms its southern boundary. For more on this story, click the link in our bio.
Follow @sarah_stacke for more stories celebrating the beauty of the Great Plains. #CheyenneRiverReservation #Lakota #MoreauRiver #GreatPlains

node.text: Photo by @mattborowick / At the top of Flagstaff Mountain in Boulder, Colorado, the view is breathtaking. Sunset over the Rocky Mountains is something everyone should get to see. You can either make the short hike from the parking lot or take a slightly longer trek from the main road. Make sure to start at the Realization Point trailhead just off Flagstaff Road. Please follow @mattborowick for more pictures like this. #colorado #sunset #nature #adventure #usa

node.text: Photo by @kahliaprilphoto / Without a breath of wind or a cloud in the sky, stars and galaxies are reflected on the mirrorlike lake in complete silence. Nights like this are pure magic! This was taken in Banff National Park.

node.text:
Photo by @daisygilardini / A bear in Alaska’s Lake Clark National Park scouts the river estuary, looking for salmon. The main difference between black bears and brown bears, or grizzlies, is not fur color. Both black and brown bears can exhibit a variety of colors. So, how to tell the two apart? 
Black bears are usually smaller, but unless you see one side by side with a brown bear, this is not much help in the field! The most obvious difference is the clearly visible shoulder hump unique to brown bears. Black bears have a straighter face profile with longer noses and taller ears; they also have shorter claws. 
Follow me @DaisyGilardini for more images and stories behind the scenes. #bear #brownbear #grizzlybear #alaska #lakeclarknationalpark

node.text: Photo by Muhammed Muheisen @mmuheisen / Meteora, a UNESCO World Heritage site in central Greece, is best known for its clifftop monasteries. For more photos and videos from different parts of the world, follow me @mmuheisen and @mmuheisenpublic. #muhammedmuheisen #Meteora #Greece

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by National Geographic Travel on July 26, 2021.

node.text:
Photo by @francescolastrucci / The village of Olympos on the remote island of Karpathos, Greece, is placed on a dramatically scenic stage as if suspended between the sea and the mountains. Olympos tells the story of a village hidden in an inaccessible territory to save itself from the dangers coming from the sea. Due to the isolation, Olympos has been able to preserve ancient traditions that have disappeared on other islands of the Aegean Sea. Now connected to the rest of the island by a long, winding road, the village is still able to preserve its magic, its dialect, and its festivities. 
Follow me @francescolastrucci for more places, daily life, and stories around the world. #karpathos #greece #landscape #dailylife

node.text:
Photo by @amivitale / Orphaned baby elephants browse and play at Reteti Elephant Sanctuary (@r.e.s.c.u.e) in northern Kenya. These elephants were rescued after being orphaned—some because of drought and environmental conditions, some because of poaching or human-wildlife conflict. They are under the care of wildlife keepers recruited from the local Samburu community. Reteti is the first ever community-owned elephant sanctuary in Africa. It provides a safe place for injured elephants to heal and later be returned back to the wild. 
Please follow @amivitale and @r.e.s.c.u.e to learn how to support them. @sararafoundation @conservationorg @kenyawildlifeservice @nrt_kenya @tusk_org @sandiegozoo @thephotosociety #elephant #saveelephants #stoppoaching #kenya #empathyiseverything

node.text:
Photo by @DaisyGilardini / Harp seals in the Gulf of St. Lawrence in Quebec, Canada, give birth to their pups in February and March on the pack ice. At birth pups are yellowish in color, but after a couple days their fur turns pure white. In the last few years poor ice conditions drove an increase in mortality rates. Scientists say that even if one year of bad ice will not compromise the species, ice patterns over time could have concerning consequences. 
Follow me @DaisyGilardini for more images and stories behind the scenes. #arctic #seal #harpseal #magdalenislands #canada

node.text: Photo by @kahliaprilphoto / Sometimes you have to embrace the bad weather. On this day I hiked high into the mountains in Canmore, Alberta, and was swallowed by clouds, without a view for the entire day. On my way back down, I got a break in the weather for about 10 minutes—long enough to enjoy this view before the clouds quickly engulfed the mountains again.
